    "• Stop-word removal: Stop-words were removed which involves a process that focuses on eliminating insignificant words from the text.",
    "Stop-words are commonly occurring words in the text that do not provide useful information and can impact classification performance.",
    "Examples of stop-words include prepositions, conjunctions, pronouns, and other similar words.",
    "• Stemming: Stemming was performed to reduce the derived features to their root or stem forms.",
    "This transformation of semantically similar features helps to reduce the feature space, minimize morphological variations in words, and enhance the classification performance of the model."
